Just go do the quest the way I outlined it on the first page of this thread. Trust me. That'll fix essentially every problem you ever have in Freeport, except for the evil guilds in the sewers...<br>
<br>
Sure, you can Rp your heart out, slaying every Freeport Militia member you encounter, but really, it's a hassle. You can't get to the Arena, you can't go take the boat, you can't wander around about 5 different zones for fear of accidentally encountering a guard who hits for 175+...<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
Oh, and I soloed Sergeant Slate yesterday. I've owed him that for quite some time now. Nearly 2 years ago, he KS'd literally every mob I could find while trying to get from level 3 to 4 in EC. As a result, getting from 3 to 4 took me over 8 hours. (And all you newer EQ members, this was long before the mob spawn rate was upped in EC, and long before light blue exp, and long long before the &quot;easy road to level 10&quot; system was in place.....)<br>
<br>
Basically I would fight a mob down to the last few hits, then Slate would run up and hit it for 175 and KS me every single time. Then I'd be battered, go sit down and try to heal, and guess who'd be there when a new fire beetle or black bear spawned nearby? Yep, Slate. He's whack them and move on....It was because of him that I went to Greater Faydark and Crushbone at that level... Ah good old Orc Hill.....<br>
<br>
The sad part is that I was forced to use 2 Soulfire charges to beat Slate. I see they've buffed up his abilities ever since the AA system was added. Yeah, why would you think that having AA points would actually make the game easier, when they just buff all the mobs to compensate? Bah.<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
